  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nSerialization/deserialization to the database is presently tightly coupled to SSZ serialization. This creates awkward and verbose code when it comes to objects with fields that should not be serialized for consensus but _should_ be serialized for stores in the DB (e.g., caches).\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nDefine some new traits (naming subject to change):\r\n\r\n- `DBItem`: defined on each top-level object and defines how that object should be stored in the database. E.g., should it be split into parts and stored separately, or should it just be stored as one big blob?\r\n- `DBEncode` & `DBDecode`: defined on each object which will be stored in the db. Defines how that object should into/from bytes for storage in the DB.\r\n",
